      <p>Katina L. Rogers is an independent scholar and educational consultant who designs creative, sustainable, and equitable structures for institutions.</p>

      <p>Her scholarly interests center on higher education reform, including scholarly communication practices, professionalization, career development, public scholarship, and labor policy advocacy. She is the author of two books: <em><a href="https://punctumbooks.com/titles/the-presence-of-absence-meditations-on-the-unsayable-in-writing/">Presence of Absence: Meditations on the Unsayable in Writing</a></em> (punctum books, 2024) and <em><a href="https://www.dukeupress.edu/putting-the-humanities-phd-to-work">Putting the Humanities PhD to Work: Thriving in and beyond the Classroom</a></em> (Duke University Press, 2020), as well as numerous articles and chapters.</p>
